WEBVTT

00:05.500 --> 00:07.166
Previously on  Billions...

00:07.250 --> 00:09.417
I sure as hell will testify
about what Chuck Rhoades did

00:09.500 --> 00:12.125
and that Charles Rhoades Sr.
was steering his own money

00:12.208 --> 00:14.291
and Chuck's money
was directly involved--

00:14.375 --> 00:15.417
Stop.

00:15.500 --> 00:17.917
I'm willing to pay you
30 million to tell the truth.

00:18.000 --> 00:19.625
You'll give my people
a statement

00:19.709 --> 00:21.750
laying out
how Rhoades did what he did.

00:22.625 --> 00:23.875
How much do I use?

00:23.959 --> 00:26.417
Just trace amounts
on my signal.

00:26.500 --> 00:28.542
Give up your so-called
license to trade.

00:28.625 --> 00:29.500
That is the only angle.

00:29.583 --> 00:31.917
I can't be seen
to be guiding the firm.

00:32.000 --> 00:33.375
It'll all be up to you.

00:33.458 --> 00:35.000
The gaming
license?

00:35.083 --> 00:37.125
They're announcing soon, and
there's sure to be a bounce.

00:37.208 --> 00:39.250
My cash happens
to be tied up

00:39.333 --> 00:41.500
in a few real estate
deals right now.

00:41.583 --> 00:43.083
Let me guess.

00:43.166 --> 00:44.208
Kingsford?

00:44.291 --> 00:46.917
"The first ship to make
a manned mission to Mars."

00:47.000 --> 00:50.750
I haven't stayed in bed
past 5 a.m. since 2001.

00:50.834 --> 00:53.166
I had
my man follow them.

00:53.250 --> 00:55.417
Look at that
morning-after glow.

00:55.500 --> 00:57.542
♪♪♪

00:57.625 --> 00:59.375
Why don't you reach out,
talk to him?

00:59.458 --> 01:00.125
If there's any
reaching out,

01:00.208 --> 01:02.250
it should be
from the other side.

01:02.333 --> 01:04.792
What, you want me to initiate,
for Christ's sake?

01:04.875 --> 01:06.959
They're in this.

01:07.041 --> 01:09.166
I can't look away
from it anymore.

01:09.250 --> 01:13.667
♪♪♪

01:18.583 --> 01:21.875
♪ dramatic music  ♪

01:21.959 --> 01:25.625
♪♪♪

01:25.709 --> 01:30.166
♪♪♪

01:30.250 --> 01:33.709
Ira Schirmer
showed us to the well.

01:33.792 --> 01:36.083
But all we had to do
was look down

01:36.166 --> 01:38.959
to see the thick
crude on our boots.

01:40.750 --> 01:42.500
We tracked the size
of your position.

01:42.583 --> 01:44.834
Matching that
of your son's trust.

01:44.917 --> 01:48.000
The timing of the additional
investment corroborates

01:48.083 --> 01:49.917
Mr. Schirmer's affidavit:

01:50.000 --> 01:53.208
Chuck directed you
to invade the trust.

01:53.291 --> 01:56.000
He baited Axelrod,
he is complicit

01:56.083 --> 01:58.625
in the sabotage
of the Ice Juice IPO.

01:58.709 --> 02:00.500
Don't say a thing

02:00.583 --> 02:03.500
until they say
the magic word.

02:03.583 --> 02:08.625
♪♪♪

02:08.709 --> 02:12.041
We are prepared
to offer you immunity.

02:12.125 --> 02:14.041
That's the one.

02:14.125 --> 02:16.250
In exchange
for your cooperation.

02:17.542 --> 02:21.917
Alternatively.
Perjury carries five years.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.458
Tell me:
You have that to spare?

02:24.542 --> 02:27.875
♪♪♪

02:27.959 --> 02:30.667
♪♪♪

02:30.750 --> 02:34.333
♪♪♪

02:38.125 --> 02:41.500
♪ suspenseful music ♪

02:41.583 --> 02:45.709
♪♪♪

02:45.792 --> 02:50.250
♪♪♪

02:50.333 --> 02:53.250
Connerty knows what Schirmer was
trying to say in our interview

02:53.333 --> 02:54.542
and is chasing it down.

02:54.625 --> 02:57.542
I wouldn't be surprised
if he talks to your father.

02:57.625 --> 02:59.750
Or already has.

02:59.834 --> 03:01.583
That's disquieting.

03:01.667 --> 03:04.166
Will your father hold up
under questioning?

03:04.250 --> 03:07.750
He's a free-radical.

03:07.834 --> 03:10.041
Not taking my counsel
at the moment.

03:10.125 --> 03:13.291
Then you have a real
and unsolvable problem.

03:15.458 --> 03:17.500
So I have to get
my father to keep quiet.

03:17.583 --> 03:20.458
And you need to remind Connerty
he has a fucking day job.

03:26.834 --> 03:30.750
♪♪♪

03:38.375 --> 03:41.834
[Sammy Davis Jr.'s
"Mr. Bojangles" plays]

03:47.208 --> 03:50.208
♪ I knew a man, Bojangles  ♪

03:50.291 --> 03:52.000
♪ And he'd dance... ♪

03:52.083 --> 03:54.625
This is some
advanced real estate play.

03:54.709 --> 03:56.834
Let the Saudis
keep 432 Park.

03:56.917 --> 03:57.959
♪ In worn-out shoes  ♪

03:58.041 --> 04:00.166
This is the real prize.

04:00.250 --> 04:02.166
The last burial plot
in Manhattan.

04:02.250 --> 04:04.625
And all the time
to enjoy it.

04:04.709 --> 04:08.291
Only 350,000,

04:08.375 --> 04:11.083
and this cool slice
of earth is mine.

04:12.291 --> 04:16.083
Well... and long
may it remain unoccupied.

04:17.041 --> 04:20.208
Mr. Axelrod.

04:20.291 --> 04:21.291
We have eyes on the three
labs in the Tri-State area

04:21.375 --> 04:23.709
capable of production
and storage

04:23.792 --> 04:25.250
-of the Ice Juice toxicant.
-FBI is interviewing

04:25.333 --> 04:27.583
the lead techs
at each of them.

04:27.667 --> 04:29.500
-They'll be onto ours soon.
-By the time

04:29.583 --> 04:31.000
they get to our lab,
make sure there is no lab.

04:31.083 --> 04:33.250
Got it.
What else?

04:33.333 --> 04:35.125
Dake is protecting Rhoades.

04:35.208 --> 04:36.709
Ira Schirmer
saw it firsthand.

04:36.792 --> 04:39.125
He also saw that Connerty,
if properly armed, won't let up.

04:39.208 --> 04:41.834
You have the
Schirmer affidavit?

04:41.917 --> 04:44.959
Deliver it tonight?

04:45.041 --> 04:45.834
Go arm him, gents.

04:45.917 --> 04:50.166
♪♪♪

04:54.458 --> 04:56.250
This is Charles Rhoades.

04:56.333 --> 04:59.083
Leave a message,
and I'll get back to you.

05:01.792 --> 05:02.750
♪ dramatic music ♪

05:09.875 --> 05:13.792
♪♪♪

05:13.875 --> 05:17.875
♪♪♪

05:17.959 --> 05:20.917
You RSVP'd no,
you hate reunions.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.166
"The dead are more present
than the living,"

05:23.250 --> 05:25.291
-I think you put it.
-Changed my mind.

05:29.583 --> 05:32.083
Connerty's aware
of my father's involvement,

05:32.166 --> 05:34.417
he's trying
for details.

05:34.500 --> 05:36.583
Hard to convince your father
to protect you

05:36.667 --> 05:38.250
when you're not
talking to him.

05:38.333 --> 05:38.834
Mm-hmm.

05:38.917 --> 05:41.750
So, uh, Yale reunion,

05:41.834 --> 05:42.834
here we come.

05:42.917 --> 05:44.583
-They're giving him an award.
-Right.

05:44.667 --> 05:48.250
Twenty-fifth and 50th are the
same night, so he'll be there...

05:48.333 --> 05:50.083
He quite enjoys
the presence of the dead.

05:50.166 --> 05:52.208
Makes him
feel victorious.

05:53.667 --> 05:55.917
You're gonna convince him.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
For me.

05:59.750 --> 06:00.625
For us.

06:00.709 --> 06:02.792
Our family, yes.

06:02.875 --> 06:04.041
We are.

06:04.834 --> 06:06.792
Together.

06:09.667 --> 06:12.500
♪ dramatic music ♪

06:12.583 --> 06:16.792
♪♪♪

06:16.875 --> 06:21.333
♪♪♪

06:22.458 --> 06:26.458
♪♪♪

06:26.542 --> 06:30.583
♪♪♪

06:34.333 --> 06:38.792
♪♪♪

06:46.375 --> 06:49.291
♪ dramatic music ♪

06:49.375 --> 06:52.542
♪♪♪

06:52.625 --> 06:55.583
♪♪♪

06:55.667 --> 06:58.208
World-Aid is poised to provide

06:58.291 --> 06:59.125
solar-powered,
air-conditioned tents

06:59.208 --> 07:01.709
to Central African nations

07:01.792 --> 07:04.000
through our new
solar tent initiative.

07:04.083 --> 07:04.959
Bobby Axelrod.

07:05.041 --> 07:06.500
Oscar Langstraat.

07:06.583 --> 07:08.583
-I know who you are.
-Good to finally

07:08.667 --> 07:11.375
-meet you in person, Bobby.
-You too.

07:11.458 --> 07:13.125
So you, um,

07:13.208 --> 07:15.333
you flew in private
to worry about a cure

07:15.417 --> 07:17.333
for overheated
Southern Africa?

07:17.417 --> 07:19.959
Well, my plane runs
on recycled corn oil,

07:20.041 --> 07:21.166
so it's all good.

07:21.250 --> 07:23.166
Ah. That's what I have
my masseuse use too.

07:27.500 --> 07:29.291
You're not as bad at this
as the articles say.

07:29.375 --> 07:31.875
-Small talk.

07:31.959 --> 07:33.375
But I can see
it's work for you.

07:33.458 --> 07:34.583
Look, these charities

07:34.667 --> 07:37.875
have basically become
feel good machines.

07:37.959 --> 07:40.542
You gave ten mill.
They'll say thanks.

07:40.625 --> 07:43.458
They'll ask again.
You'll give again.

07:43.542 --> 07:44.250
But at the coming
board meeting

07:44.333 --> 07:47.500
I'm pitching
a drastic shift.

07:47.583 --> 07:50.208
I think that World-Aid
should own  the company

07:50.291 --> 07:51.500
that makes
the solar panels.

07:51.583 --> 07:52.667
-Rayveon Solar.
-Right.

07:52.750 --> 07:55.959
That way, when the panels
go into wide use,

07:56.041 --> 07:57.417
World-Aid itself
profits from it,

07:57.500 --> 08:00.208
grows, becomes
self-sustaining.

08:00.291 --> 08:01.250
Venture Philanthropy.

08:01.333 --> 08:03.125
There's some of that
disruption you're famous for.

08:03.208 --> 08:04.500
Disruption works.

08:04.583 --> 08:07.375
It's uncomfortable
but effective.

08:07.458 --> 08:09.000
-Like rolfing.
-I don't know.

08:09.083 --> 08:11.875
You might be able to sell
that shit out by the Bay, but--

08:11.959 --> 08:14.875
Venture Philanthropy
is the future.

08:14.959 --> 08:18.083
I sought you out because
I want your support

08:18.166 --> 08:19.542
when I bring this
to the board.

08:19.625 --> 08:22.375
My support isn't
gonna help.

08:22.458 --> 08:24.125
The folks on
the World-Aid board,

08:24.208 --> 08:26.041
they aren't in it
for the future.

08:26.125 --> 08:28.417
They like the access
and the status it gives them.

08:28.500 --> 08:29.542
And they don't want
to lose it.

08:29.625 --> 08:33.750
Their risk tolerance
is exactly zero.

08:33.834 --> 08:34.792
Coach Tikhonov
in Lake Placid.

08:36.959 --> 08:39.417
That's a sport ball
analogy, right?

08:39.500 --> 08:40.834
Ok.

08:40.917 --> 08:42.250
The future hurts.

08:42.333 --> 08:43.917
But only once.

08:44.000 --> 08:46.875
Denying it
stings forever.

08:46.959 --> 08:49.250
Like Shelob
in Cirith Ungol.

08:49.333 --> 08:51.834
Oh, that's a Middle
Earth/fantasy analogy, right?

08:51.917 --> 08:54.166
Ok.

08:54.250 --> 08:56.083
But the board doesn't
take to outsiders

08:56.166 --> 08:57.709
telling them
how to do their job.

09:00.125 --> 09:03.417
I bear an
unpleasant communiqué:

09:03.500 --> 09:05.834
Due to your
legal entanglements,

09:05.917 --> 09:08.458
the chairman has asked
that I  represent

09:08.542 --> 09:11.417
the Axelrod Foundation
on the dais... in your stead.

09:11.500 --> 09:14.083
I remember a time
when ten million

09:14.166 --> 09:17.166
got you on
the main stage...

09:17.250 --> 09:18.125
Go ahead, Ayles.

09:18.208 --> 09:22.250
♪ dramatic music ♪

09:22.333 --> 09:23.917
And there it is:

09:24.000 --> 09:25.709
The only person
the board mistrusts

09:25.792 --> 09:28.875
more than someone
like you, is me.

09:30.250 --> 09:33.709
But I'm still
on the board.

09:33.792 --> 09:35.709
So I'll consider
your proposal.

09:35.792 --> 09:39.875
♪♪♪

09:50.583 --> 09:53.709
Good day to you.

09:53.792 --> 09:57.500
I come bearing tithe.
And a lot of it.

09:57.583 --> 09:59.709
And is this gift
unencumbered?

09:59.792 --> 10:03.208
Once I get what I came here for,
use it how you'd like.

10:03.291 --> 10:06.792
I want to secure the available
burial plot, for all time.

10:06.875 --> 10:09.834
I'm afraid there is
no available burial plot.

10:09.917 --> 10:11.500
Who snaked me?

10:11.583 --> 10:14.792
An individual who had a prior
relationship with the Church.

10:18.166 --> 10:20.041
I don't suppose
you could tell me who--

10:20.125 --> 10:21.333
Sorry.

10:27.208 --> 10:29.041
I knocked
on your office door.

10:29.125 --> 10:30.291
You weren't there.

10:30.375 --> 10:33.291
It's all one big office, Oliver.
Committed as we are.

10:33.375 --> 10:36.000
So you must be interviewing
that lab tech?

10:36.083 --> 10:37.041
Later.

10:37.125 --> 10:38.458
I'm about to interview
another prime suspect.

10:38.542 --> 10:41.583
Are you?
Don't get waylaid.

10:41.667 --> 10:43.375
Axelrod is the bullseye.

10:45.208 --> 10:47.750
And the green ring
around it, too,

10:47.834 --> 10:49.000
whatever that's called.

10:49.083 --> 10:50.250
The single bull.

10:50.333 --> 10:51.083
Yeah.

10:51.166 --> 10:54.709
That's Axelrod.
The single bull.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.417
Mr. Rhoades.

11:15.458 --> 11:17.750
Brace a man while
he's grooming himself,

11:17.834 --> 11:21.250
hope the intimacy
makes him feel vulnerable.

11:21.333 --> 11:23.417
An admirable tactic,
Bryan.

11:23.500 --> 11:25.208
This is a respectful
courtesy call.

11:25.291 --> 11:28.125
I'm letting you know,
before anyone  braces you:

11:28.208 --> 11:30.500
We're aware of your involvement
in the Ice Juice IPO.

11:30.583 --> 11:33.583
I've known Ira Schirmer
for years.

11:33.667 --> 11:34.959
As my son's college roommate,
then lawyer.

11:35.041 --> 11:37.583
So I threw a little capital
behind the boy's venture.

11:37.667 --> 11:39.458
Not much more to it
than that.

11:39.542 --> 11:41.917
Yeah, that's how
it'd look

11:42.000 --> 11:43.417
if Ira weren't prepared
to testify

11:43.500 --> 11:46.709
about what really went on.

11:47.834 --> 11:49.625
Well, I guess, you wait

11:49.709 --> 11:53.000
for someone to embarrass
himself, he will.

11:53.083 --> 11:56.417
We just need you to confirm
what Ira said:

11:56.500 --> 11:58.166
Chuck directed you
to invade his trust

11:58.250 --> 12:02.542
and knowingly participated
in the sabotage of the company.

12:05.625 --> 12:08.125
You must think
I'm a physical moron.

12:08.208 --> 12:10.291
That's Victorian
for retard, understand.

12:10.375 --> 12:12.333
-Mm.
-You want me to testify

12:12.417 --> 12:14.000
against my son.
At my peril.

12:14.083 --> 12:17.792
And you don't even tender
the reach

12:17.875 --> 12:19.917
-If I had that to offer--
-You would have.

12:20.000 --> 12:23.875
But you don't. Which is
too bad for both of us.

12:25.375 --> 12:28.583
Maybe I'm as tired
as you are of my son's moves.

12:28.667 --> 12:32.792
Maybe I'd even like
to burn him down.

12:32.875 --> 12:36.250
But we are
a long way from that.

12:37.959 --> 12:40.000
Now...

12:40.083 --> 12:42.500
if you want
to continue this,

12:42.583 --> 12:44.583
we can do so in there.

12:45.917 --> 12:48.667
Otherwise,
I'm done with you.

12:48.750 --> 12:50.917
♪ dramatic music ♪

12:58.625 --> 12:59.500
Why does this keep
happening to me...?

12:59.583 --> 13:02.041
♪ pensive music ♪

13:02.125 --> 13:03.792
I want you
to introduce Taylor

13:03.875 --> 13:05.875
-to Rayveon Solar.
-The solar panels...

13:05.959 --> 13:08.417
If we can make
the World-Aid board invest,

13:08.500 --> 13:10.041
that stock will
go through the roof.

13:10.125 --> 13:12.166
So we need to be in position.
It's gonna be huge.

13:12.250 --> 13:14.125
And I want it in the main fund
when I'm back.

13:14.208 --> 13:16.041
-Then it'll be done.
-I can't be seen

13:16.125 --> 13:19.166
as steering Taylor, so put it
in front of them. But don't.

13:19.250 --> 13:21.208
What if we have
Ayles do it?

13:21.291 --> 13:22.709
Dress it up
like it's charity.

13:22.792 --> 13:23.667
He's the most subtle
man we've got.

13:23.750 --> 13:25.583
-Yeah. Good.
-Yeah, but what if Taylor

13:25.667 --> 13:27.709
senses you're behind it?

13:27.792 --> 13:29.542
Will they steer away?

13:29.625 --> 13:32.083
Well, all depends on what
has the stronger pull:

13:32.166 --> 13:33.834
fear or money.

13:33.917 --> 13:35.500
We'll find out
when we find out.

13:35.583 --> 13:38.375
Eventually, all comes clear.

13:38.458 --> 13:40.000
Speaking of eventuality...

13:40.083 --> 13:41.792
somebody got cozy
in my forever-bed

13:41.875 --> 13:43.709
before I had
the chance to secure it.

13:43.792 --> 13:47.542
Can I use your team of ninjas
to help me find out who?

13:47.625 --> 13:49.875
You know
they're kind of occupied

13:49.959 --> 13:51.542
with bigger shit
right now.

13:53.834 --> 13:58.000
But... what could be bigger

13:58.083 --> 13:58.959
than your eternal
resting place?

14:01.000 --> 14:01.917
Go ahead.

14:02.000 --> 14:04.583
The countdown clock is

14:04.667 --> 14:06.208
T-minus eight hours
to launch

14:06.291 --> 14:10.000
on tech titan Craig Heidecker's
first ride into space

14:10.083 --> 14:11.250
and to the
International Space Station.

14:11.333 --> 14:13.917
This is the first stage
in Heidecker's ambitious plan

14:14.000 --> 14:17.583
for an eventual manned
mission to Mars.

14:17.667 --> 14:18.750
Heidecker acquired...

14:18.834 --> 14:20.917
And the papers want to
know whose shirts he wears.

14:21.000 --> 14:24.166
How did we ever think
to short that smile?

14:24.250 --> 14:26.709
His charm is a liability.
It means people believe

14:26.792 --> 14:28.792
whatever he tells them.
And he believes it, too.

14:28.875 --> 14:30.875
It ends up having
a washing machine effect.

14:30.959 --> 14:34.166
The stock will,
pardon me, skyrocket

14:34.250 --> 14:35.417
once he hard-docks
at the Space Station.

14:35.500 --> 14:37.375
Size it down?

14:37.458 --> 14:39.375
Farpoint scrubbed
the last three launches.

14:39.458 --> 14:42.291
Guidance and navigation
each time, no corrections found.

14:42.375 --> 14:44.166
Another scrub sets them
back two years.

14:44.250 --> 14:45.083
Stock will dump,
and they'll be

14:45.166 --> 14:47.625
extra cautious
with the CEO aboard...

14:47.709 --> 14:48.834
Size up on the short.

14:48.917 --> 14:50.792
I will.
Can I be honest?

14:50.875 --> 14:51.917
I'll be honest.

14:52.000 --> 14:54.583
I'm rooting for him
to get there.

14:57.041 --> 14:58.083
I am too.

14:58.166 --> 15:01.917
First step is the ISS.
Next, space colonization.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.875
My bet is against
his business model.

15:03.959 --> 15:05.208
Not his vision.

15:05.291 --> 15:06.125
Right on.

15:06.208 --> 15:07.750
You give, we match!

15:07.834 --> 15:09.917
During the GiveBack
Charity Drive.

15:10.000 --> 15:13.625
The largesse of Axe Capital
on display, base to tip.

15:13.709 --> 15:15.166
Unless you don't give.

15:15.250 --> 15:18.375
In which case we're matching
thin fucking air.

15:18.458 --> 15:20.208
-The e-mail was received.
-I gave.

15:20.291 --> 15:21.125
I saw the amount.

15:21.208 --> 15:22.000
If that's giving,

15:22.083 --> 15:24.166
I weep for the women
in your life.

15:24.250 --> 15:25.792
The Axelrod Foundation
means well.

15:25.875 --> 15:27.500
But is intrinsically
inefficient.

15:27.583 --> 15:30.583
I put my resources to good use,
when I find a deserving outlet.

15:30.667 --> 15:32.125
Or are you not asking?

15:32.208 --> 15:33.500
No, no, I get it.

15:33.583 --> 15:35.291
Everyone from
your prom date to PETA

