I will do my best to bring it
to you in a civilized manner.

34:34.875 --> 34:39.291
♪♪♪

34:39.375 --> 34:43.500
♪♪♪

34:43.583 --> 34:48.000
♪♪♪

34:48.083 --> 34:51.500
♪♪♪

34:51.583 --> 34:54.125
Ahh.

34:56.208 --> 34:59.458
I told you
about my first time.

35:00.166 --> 35:02.333
-With the junior--
-Yes.

35:02.417 --> 35:03.834
Yes. Wasn't so.

35:03.917 --> 35:07.041
She was
my first amateur.

35:07.125 --> 35:10.834
Uncle Maurice
took me to a brothel

35:10.917 --> 35:13.500
on my fourteenth birthday.

35:13.583 --> 35:15.041
So young.

35:15.125 --> 35:17.500
That's practically
Kevin's age.

35:17.583 --> 35:18.834
Yeah.

35:22.000 --> 35:26.250
I was as ashamed
as I was nervous

35:26.333 --> 35:28.166
as I was excited.

35:29.208 --> 35:33.959
And Uncle Maurice swore it would
be between me and him...

35:34.041 --> 35:37.917
But when I got home, my father
was waiting up for me.

35:38.000 --> 35:40.542
And he knew
all about it.

35:40.625 --> 35:43.375
Told me he'd  picked
Ginger for me,

35:43.458 --> 35:47.667
that he knew  she'd
get the job done right.

35:47.750 --> 35:49.083
Take me "'round the world."

35:49.166 --> 35:53.000
You discovered
he was unfaithful.

35:53.083 --> 35:54.458
Mm-hmm.

35:55.792 --> 35:58.250
And it was the first time

35:58.333 --> 36:02.291
my father ever said
he was proud of me.

36:02.375 --> 36:06.291
♪♪♪

36:06.375 --> 36:10.333
♪♪♪

36:10.417 --> 36:14.291
♪♪♪

36:14.375 --> 36:16.333
So...How was Ginger?

36:19.208 --> 36:22.083
Well, Dad was right
about that.

36:22.166 --> 36:24.583
Yeah. She took me
'round the world.

36:27.834 --> 36:28.333
Ohh.

36:30.834 --> 36:31.625
Yeah?

36:31.709 --> 36:32.834
It's happening.

36:32.917 --> 36:34.834
Your father
is being brought in.

36:34.917 --> 36:36.583
All on the record now.

36:36.667 --> 36:37.583
You'd better
prepare yourself.

36:39.875 --> 36:43.083
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

36:48.250 --> 36:50.500
Connerty's got my father.

36:50.583 --> 36:52.709
Hm.

36:52.792 --> 36:55.792
This evening
was a misstep.

36:55.875 --> 36:59.542
I should know the man by now.
Anticipate his reactions.

36:59.625 --> 37:02.125
Not act on
what I hope them to be.

37:02.208 --> 37:04.959
You do know your father.
And how he responds.

37:05.041 --> 37:06.375
All too well.

37:06.458 --> 37:08.166
That's right. I do.

37:08.250 --> 37:09.959
And you need to use that.

37:10.041 --> 37:11.834
Exploit it.

37:11.917 --> 37:14.959
♪♪♪

37:15.041 --> 37:18.417
♪♪♪

37:20.792 --> 37:22.083
Just occurred to me.

37:22.166 --> 37:25.291
We only sup when
difficulties are at hand.

37:25.375 --> 37:28.834
But perhaps this time
is different?

37:31.041 --> 37:33.333
My father's
going to serve me up.

37:33.417 --> 37:37.959
So you may need a new horse
for the governorship.

37:38.041 --> 37:42.166
Well, only so if you're
willing to surrender.

37:42.250 --> 37:42.667
Are you?

37:42.750 --> 37:45.792
I am not, willingly.

37:45.875 --> 37:49.166
But circumstance
may cost me it.

37:49.250 --> 37:51.667
I have tried

37:51.750 --> 37:54.458
almost all manner
of appeal.

37:54.542 --> 37:55.583
Almost all...

37:58.417 --> 38:01.875
Well, then I believe
Joe Scolari can be of help.

38:01.959 --> 38:03.667
Your father's Kingsford land

38:03.750 --> 38:05.500
is in the good
state senator's domain.

38:05.583 --> 38:09.917
Which presently works
in your father's favor.

38:10.000 --> 38:12.000
But that can change.

38:15.166 --> 38:19.083
To do so, however, would be
a move you cannot walk back.

38:21.917 --> 38:24.041
So, are you sure?

38:24.125 --> 38:25.834
♪♪♪

38:25.917 --> 38:29.458
♪♪♪

38:29.542 --> 38:31.417
Craig Heidecker's
wristwatch

38:31.500 --> 38:32.583
contained 456 pieces.

38:32.667 --> 38:34.333
Inside a 38 millimeter case.

38:34.417 --> 38:37.208
Hand assembled by one horologist
over the course of a year.

38:37.291 --> 38:40.083
Some of the pieces are invisible
to the naked eye.

38:40.166 --> 38:42.750
It's precise to plus or minus
point-five seconds a day.

38:42.834 --> 38:46.667
As close to faultless precision
as possible.

38:46.750 --> 38:48.542
That's how he lived.

38:48.625 --> 38:50.125
I know how he lived.

38:52.250 --> 38:54.333
We, uh...

38:54.417 --> 38:56.917
worked together.
Briefly.

39:02.834 --> 39:05.792
Look, he understood

39:05.875 --> 39:08.583
precision is an objective,
not an end.

39:08.667 --> 39:10.250
It's what gets one as near
to perfect as possible.

39:10.333 --> 39:15.125
But perfection
is unobtainable.

39:15.208 --> 39:17.500
That's hard
for you to accept

39:17.583 --> 39:21.208
because in some areas
it is within your grasp.

39:21.291 --> 39:22.667
Math is perfect.

39:22.750 --> 39:23.750
And he did the math.

39:23.834 --> 39:26.417
A thousand times a day,
a thousand days in advance.

39:26.500 --> 39:28.959
Before he put his life
inside that vessel. I am sure.

39:29.041 --> 39:31.917
But there's always "X."
The unknown.

39:32.000 --> 39:33.250
A buildup of oxygen
in the aluminum liner.

39:33.333 --> 39:36.291
Can't be solved for.
He'd know this too.

39:36.375 --> 39:38.583
And he decided
the risk was worth it.

39:38.667 --> 39:39.959
The success of that mission

39:40.041 --> 39:41.250
would determine the viability
of his vision:

39:41.333 --> 39:44.000
To make the universe
hospitable.

39:44.083 --> 39:44.583
Because we'll need it
to be.

39:47.125 --> 39:48.041
I knew the risk
was too great.

39:48.125 --> 39:50.875
The signs read this way.
And I bet against him.

39:52.709 --> 39:55.709
He wanted to save
our lives...

39:55.792 --> 39:57.583
I profited off his death.

39:59.000 --> 40:02.959
You lost a hero
and were rewarded for it.

40:03.041 --> 40:05.417
These things
are in conflict.

40:07.458 --> 40:09.959
But conflicting emotions
require we  resolve the conflict.

40:10.041 --> 40:12.208
Can they be resolved?

40:12.291 --> 40:13.625
One emotion
has to prevail.

40:13.709 --> 40:16.125
Otherwise you languish
while the dispute carries on

40:16.208 --> 40:19.417
and you miss opportunities.

40:21.333 --> 40:24.125
It's normal to feel
two things at once.

40:24.208 --> 40:26.500
But when you're here.

40:26.583 --> 40:30.041
Mind the truth
that makes you money.

40:30.125 --> 40:34.500
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

40:37.125 --> 40:39.542
I brought pie.
So to speak...

40:39.625 --> 40:41.333
Seeing as
we'll be neighbors.

40:41.417 --> 40:42.417
Oh, it's you.

40:42.500 --> 40:44.291
The plot is spoken for.

40:44.375 --> 40:45.333
Nussfaur?

40:45.417 --> 40:46.375
I heard you're
on your ass.

40:46.458 --> 40:49.709
You can't afford
a choice patch like this.

40:50.333 --> 40:52.333
That's fucking hilarious,

40:52.417 --> 40:54.375
considering my wire
has already been sent.

40:54.458 --> 40:55.667
Is that right?

40:55.750 --> 40:57.417
Just here to sign.

40:57.500 --> 40:58.667
You can kiss my red eye
on my way out.

40:58.750 --> 41:03.041
Things I'm hearing, I'd check
the wire if I were you...

41:03.125 --> 41:05.333
Knock yourself out.

41:08.792 --> 41:13.417
It...appears his--your deposit
has been retracted.

41:13.500 --> 41:15.000
There's insufficient funds.

41:15.083 --> 41:17.333
That's bullshit!

41:17.417 --> 41:19.959
I keep 350
in my car ashtray.

41:20.041 --> 41:21.542
Sir, if you can't pay--

41:21.625 --> 41:23.458
I can and I did.

41:23.542 --> 41:24.959
Probably over extended.

41:25.041 --> 41:27.375
His marriage is collapsing
like the walls of Jericho.

41:27.458 --> 41:30.375
Where'd you get
that crap?

41:30.458 --> 41:33.542
I read about you being outed
with your mistress on Page Six.

41:33.959 --> 41:35.834
May I?

41:36.125 --> 41:38.709
Shit!

41:38.792 --> 41:41.667
I'll have you hoisted by
your scrotum for this, Wagner.

41:44.125 --> 41:46.125
So now you have
a vacancy.

41:48.291 --> 41:50.917
And now you don't.

41:54.500 --> 41:56.417
You leave boards
all the time.

41:56.500 --> 41:59.125
Yeah. When I  fucking
choose to.

41:59.208 --> 42:00.375
I don't choose
to leave this one.

42:00.458 --> 42:03.083
So you're not gonna
go gracefully.

42:03.166 --> 42:05.000
I am going
into that room,

42:05.083 --> 42:06.792
and I am gonna play
duck duck goose.

42:06.875 --> 42:08.583
I'm gonna remind each
and every fucking one of them

42:08.667 --> 42:11.917
how I've personally
enriched them.

42:12.000 --> 42:13.000
And I am calling in
the return.

42:13.083 --> 42:15.750
There's little to be gained
by instigating foes.

42:15.834 --> 42:19.000
Then they will be taught
there is no strength in numbers.

42:19.083 --> 42:20.458
Fats McCarthy,

42:20.542 --> 42:23.667
he killed 22 Germans
and captured fifty.

42:23.750 --> 42:26.625
A half-kilometer of a trench
by his own hand.

42:26.709 --> 42:27.375
I can take
this fucking board.

42:27.458 --> 42:29.166
So you're an army of one?

42:29.250 --> 42:31.250
And fortified.

42:31.333 --> 42:36.667
♪ suspenseful music  ♪

42:36.750 --> 42:38.166
There is  a toxicity

42:38.250 --> 42:40.208
that comes with being
charged with a crime.

42:41.583 --> 42:43.500
Sure, it may matter
to people in finance,

42:43.583 --> 42:45.625
but their reputations
are buttressed by money.

42:45.709 --> 42:47.417
Philanthropies only  have
their reputation.

42:47.500 --> 42:51.417
And you are a threat
to theirs.

42:51.500 --> 42:53.959
It's like academia.
Everything's a big fucking deal,

42:54.041 --> 42:55.917
because the stakes
are so small...

42:59.458 --> 43:02.834
So this is where
we live now--

43:02.917 --> 43:05.000
in retreat.

43:05.083 --> 43:07.000
We fall back.
We preserve.

43:07.083 --> 43:08.417
We defend.

43:08.500 --> 43:13.417
♪♪♪

43:13.500 --> 43:14.792
♪♪♪

43:14.875 --> 43:16.750
It'll pass when
you clear your name.

43:16.834 --> 43:19.333
But for now,
you need to embrace

43:19.417 --> 43:22.750
the victory of self-awareness.
Because out in the world,

43:22.834 --> 43:24.917
you might keep taking
losses for awhile.

43:26.917 --> 43:27.750
That's where you're at.

43:31.625 --> 43:32.709
We both are.

43:49.583 --> 43:51.208
I'd like to push
the final item

43:51.291 --> 43:52.208
to the top of
the agenda.

43:52.291 --> 43:54.542
Changing the agenda requires
a unanimous vote.

43:54.625 --> 43:56.834
I'll expedite:
you don't have it.

43:59.041 --> 44:01.375
Fine.

44:01.458 --> 44:03.041
First order.

44:03.125 --> 44:05.625
Oscar Langstraat, one of
our most important donors,

44:05.709 --> 44:09.041
would like to address
the board regarding a...

44:09.125 --> 44:11.375
Venture Philanthropy
initiative.

44:11.458 --> 44:12.875
Thank you.

44:12.959 --> 44:14.166
I value your good works.

44:14.250 --> 44:19.166
But organizations must change,
because the world is changing.

44:19.250 --> 44:22.875
Venture Philanthropy, conducted
with precision and care,

44:22.959 --> 44:24.208
is that change.

44:24.291 --> 44:25.542
We'll need
those tents in here,

44:25.625 --> 44:28.458
you keep pumping in
the fucking hot air.

44:28.542 --> 44:30.250
There'll be no crosstalk.

44:30.333 --> 44:33.291
So I'll  just talk.

44:33.375 --> 44:35.834
Venture Philanthropy
can work.

44:35.917 --> 44:40.000
But it requires a rigorous
level of oversight.

44:40.083 --> 44:42.709
This group isn't
built for that.

44:43.834 --> 44:46.083
Then what are we
built for, Axelrod?

44:46.166 --> 44:47.709
Listen, Langstraat,
I'd love to let you burn them,

44:47.792 --> 44:51.083
in the name of burnishing
your own rep.

44:51.166 --> 44:54.583
But I cannot let you hurt the
people of sub-Saharan Africa

44:54.667 --> 44:58.083
just so you can be part of yet
one more cutting edge movement.

44:58.166 --> 44:59.667
Wake up, Axelrod.

44:59.750 --> 45:01.583
Cystic fibrosis is on
the verge of being treatable,

45:01.667 --> 45:04.250
or even curable,
thanks to VP.

45:04.333 --> 45:05.792
They've created a way

45:05.875 --> 45:07.458
to earn the money
they need for research

45:07.542 --> 45:09.667
instead of endlessly
fundraising.

45:09.750 --> 45:14.625
Look. Don't try and reinvent
who we are, here.

45:14.709 --> 45:18.166
There is a reason
for the tried and true--

45:18.250 --> 45:20.041
it may not be perfect,
but it works.

45:21.875 --> 45:25.417
Look, you will make
fools of yourselves.

45:25.500 --> 45:27.917
A 50 million dollar
investment in Rayveon Solar

45:28.000 --> 45:30.041
would allow
the people to bypass

45:30.125 --> 45:31.792
Africa's failed
electric grid

45:31.875 --> 45:33.917
in the way cellphones
bypassed its phone lines.

45:34.000 --> 45:37.792
They'll be able to power homes,
businesses, indoor farms--

45:37.875 --> 45:39.375
Like the bard says:

45:39.458 --> 45:43.000
save the bold moves
for the brilliant players.

45:43.083 --> 45:45.125
That ain't you.

45:45.208 --> 45:46.417
And it sure as shit isn't

45:46.500 --> 45:48.333
anybody sitting around
this table.

45:48.417 --> 45:51.417
Spoken like the overpaid
day trader you are.

45:51.500 --> 45:53.583
So says the fucking

45:53.667 --> 45:55.750
Northern California
pipe dreamer.

45:55.834 --> 45:57.500
Don't do it, people.

46:00.583 --> 46:04.000
Mr. Langstraat's proposal
goes to a vote.

46:04.083 --> 46:06.834
Those in favor
of establishing a fund

46:06.917 --> 46:09.166
for the purpose
of venture investment.

46:09.250 --> 46:11.625
As I, for one,
certainly am...

46:14.917 --> 46:17.709
You're making
a bigtime fucking mistake...

46:17.792 --> 46:22.625
♪♪♪

46:22.709 --> 46:23.083
The motion passes.

46:25.834 --> 46:29.000
As will, I expect,
the next.

46:29.083 --> 46:30.166
I motion to remove
Robert Axelrod

46:30.250 --> 46:34.000
from the World-Aid Consortium
Board of Directors.

46:34.083 --> 46:35.208
Those in favor.

46:35.291 --> 46:40.041
♪♪♪

46:40.125 --> 46:42.333
The Board thanks you
for your contribution.

46:56.917 --> 47:00.166
To what do I owe
the pleasure of a visit

47:00.250 --> 47:02.041
from the only state senator
who matters?

47:02.125 --> 47:06.458
I felt it was only right
to let you know personally:

47:06.542 --> 47:08.125
The Kingsford land

47:08.208 --> 47:13.333
may need to be reassigned
as a conservation area.

47:15.792 --> 47:18.709
Eastern elk need
all the help they can get.

47:18.792 --> 47:23.000
Delicate species,
require a certain habitat.

47:23.083 --> 47:27.083
Whereas a casino,
like a fungus,

47:27.166 --> 47:29.875
will thrive
in any dank climate.

47:32.750 --> 47:37.375
If the casino moves,
my land up there is worthless.

47:37.458 --> 47:40.917
This is some overreach
of the canton, Joe.

47:44.834 --> 47:49.583
Eastern elk need
all the help they can get.

47:49.667 --> 47:50.709
Delicate species.

47:50.792 --> 47:53.750
Require a certain
habitat.

47:53.834 --> 47:57.583
♪♪♪

47:59.166 --> 48:02.166
We are prepared
to offer you immunity

48:02.250 --> 48:04.875
in exchange
for your cooperation.

48:04.959 --> 48:09.458
Alternatively. Perjury
carries five years.

48:09.542 --> 48:11.291
Tell me: You have
that to spare?

48:11.375 --> 48:16.875
♪♪♪

48:16.959 --> 48:21.625
♪♪♪

48:23.583 --> 48:26.250
Ira is a liar.

48:27.875 --> 48:31.917
A disgruntled,
failed investor.

48:32.000 --> 48:36.709
I touched my son's money
because I saw a win.

48:36.792 --> 48:38.500
I believed it was
within the scope

48:38.583 --> 48:41.500
of my power as Trustee.

48:41.583 --> 48:44.458
Chuck was my victim.

48:44.542 --> 48:47.625
And we were both victims
of Bobby Axelrod.

48:47.709 --> 48:49.750
Do you know what happens

48:49.834 --> 48:51.166
when that statement gets
rebutted in open court?

48:51.250 --> 48:56.834
I don't want to put you
in jail, sir, but I will.

48:56.917 --> 49:00.667
♪♪♪

49:00.750 --> 49:04.750
♪♪♪

49:04.834 --> 49:08.667
♪♪♪

49:08.750 --> 49:10.875
We've both loved
this man--

49:10.959 --> 49:14.750
you as his father,
me as a sort of son.

49:14.834 --> 49:18.333
But it's time to do
what's right.

49:23.208 --> 49:27.000
I would've thought
that my son trained you better

49:27.083 --> 49:29.291
than to rely on emotion,

49:29.375 --> 49:33.250
when only true fortitude
will get the job done...

49:37.875 --> 49:41.375
You have my statement,
buckeroo.

49:41.458 --> 49:45.542
♪♪♪

49:45.625 --> 49:49.709
♪♪♪

49:53.959 --> 49:57.583
Well. I gave you
your shot with him.

49:57.667 --> 49:59.959
Now, pick back up
on the other witnesses.

50:00.041 --> 50:03.041
♪♪♪

50:03.125 --> 50:06.250
♪♪♪

50:10.000 --> 50:10.792
Do you carry this model?

50:10.875 --> 50:13.750
The 5270R
in rose gold.

50:13.834 --> 50:15.083
We do have one.

50:15.166 --> 50:19.250
♪♪♪

50:19.333 --> 50:23.291
♪♪♪

50:23.375 --> 50:24.792
Perpetual Calendar
chronograph.

50:24.875 --> 50:28.083
Silvery opaline dial.

50:28.166 --> 50:30.208
Day, month and leap year
in apertures.

50:30.291 --> 50:33.375
Moon phase...

50:33.458 --> 50:36.417
Sapphire-crystal case back
with hinged dustcover.

50:36.500 --> 50:39.125
Fold-over clasp
in 18 karat rose gold.

50:41.083 --> 50:44.750
164,400 dollars.

50:44.834 --> 50:46.291
You're welcome
to try it on--

50:46.375 --> 50:47.500
I'll take it.

50:53.667 --> 50:56.250
Nice piece.

50:56.333 --> 50:58.375
I'd forgotten what
your voice sounds like.

50:58.458 --> 51:00.083
Because I only heard it
through Wags. Ayles.

51:00.166 --> 51:03.458
You had them work me
on the tent initiative...

51:03.542 --> 51:04.750
The message was received.
I saw the play.

51:04.834 --> 51:07.125
Well enough to act on it?

51:08.041 --> 51:09.875
I bought a basket of solar
to obscure it--

51:09.959 --> 51:11.500
ten names--
including Rayveon.

51:11.583 --> 51:12.709
Good.

51:12.792 --> 51:14.625
The board approved
the venture fund.

51:14.709 --> 51:16.208
Rayveon Solar
is churning panels

51:16.291 --> 51:17.792
out of Shenzhen
right now.

51:17.875 --> 51:18.667
Your play all along.

51:18.750 --> 51:20.041
Get the board
to expand the initiative.

51:20.125 --> 51:23.291
Axe Cap reaps the win
on manufacturing.

51:23.375 --> 51:25.792
Your aim is true.
So is mine.

51:25.875 --> 51:26.834
Heidecker.

51:26.917 --> 51:28.667
Farpoint stock price went
the way of its founder.

51:28.750 --> 51:30.667
Our short paid big.

51:34.709 --> 51:36.834
About halfway through
your screed, I realized:

51:36.917 --> 51:38.375
You weren't insulting me.

51:38.458 --> 51:39.542
We were dancing.

51:39.625 --> 51:42.250
Well, I couldn't
rid myself of my toxicity

51:42.333 --> 51:43.875
so I aimed it.

51:43.959 --> 51:46.166
For my benefit.
They hate you so much,

51:46.250 --> 51:48.625
they forgot that
they hate me too.

51:48.709 --> 51:50.583
Thank you for throwing
the vote my way.

51:50.667 --> 51:52.083
My pleasure.

51:52.166 --> 51:53.166
Oh, I imagine it is.

51:53.250 --> 51:55.083
